  "prompt": "How many milliliters of liguid b-6 vitamins are in 85 milligrams of b-6 vitamin?",
  "response": "To determine how many milliliters of liquid B-6 vitamins correspond to 85 milligrams of vitamin B-6, you need to know the concentration of the B-6 vitamin solution you are using. \n\nFor example, if you have a solution that has a concentration of 10 mg/mL, then:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Volume (mL)} = \\frac{\\text{Amount (mg)}}{\\text{Concentration (mg/mL)}}\n\\]\n\nUsing our example concentration:\n\n\\[\n\\text{Volume (mL)} = \\frac{85 \\text{ mg}}{10 \\text{ mg/mL}} = 8.5 \\text{ mL}\n\\]\n\nIf you know the specific concentration of your B-6 vitamin liquid, you can use the formula above to calculate the volume in milliliters. Please provide or verify the concentration for an accurate calculation.",
